From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matti Viljanen <matti.viljanen@jolla.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 17:46:20 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Use consistent soname version

zxing-cpp bumped soname version without changing application version,
which somehow breaks automatic dependencies in packages using it.
Fix it simply by setting the package major version as the soname.
---
 core/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/core/CMakeLists.txt b/core/CMakeLists.txt
index bd152ca9..19793200 100644
--- a/core/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/core/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@ cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.16)
 
 project (ZXing VERSION "3.0.2")
 set (ZXING_VERSION_SUFFIX "")
-set (ZXING_SONAME 4) # see https://github.com/zxing-cpp/zxing-cpp/issues/333
+set (ZXING_SONAME 3) # see https://github.com/zxing-cpp/zxing-cpp/issues/333
 
 option (ZXING_USE_BUNDLED_ZINT "Use the bundled libzint for barcode creation/writing" ON)
 foreach(format 1D AZTEC DATAMATRIX MAXICODE PDF417 QRCODE)
